# Design Rules (Apple-inspired)

## Core Principles

- Clean and minimal — remove anything that doesn't serve a purpose
- Generous whitespace — when in doubt, add more padding
- Subtle over dramatic — light borders, soft shadows, gentle transitions
- Single accent color — never compete with multiple strong colors
- Typography-first hierarchy — use weight and size, not color, to create hierarchy

## Tailwind Usage

- Use CSS variables from index.css over raw colors
  - ✅ bg-background, text-foreground, border-border
  - ❌ bg-white, text-black, border-gray-200

## Spacing Scale

- Tight spacing: gap-2, p-2 (8px)
- Default spacing: gap-4, p-4 (16px)
- Loose spacing: gap-6, p-6 (24px)
- Section spacing: gap-8, p-8 (32px)

## Common Patterns

```tsx
// Card
<div className="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm">

// Page container
<div className="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-8">

// Section title
<h2 className="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">

// Muted label
<p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">

// Primary button
<button className="rounded-lg bg-primary px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground transition-opacity hover:opacity-90">
```

## Animation

- Use transition-* for hover/focus states
- Duration: 150ms for micro, 300ms for layout
- Easing: ease-out for entrances, ease-in for exits

## Responsive

- Mobile-first: base styles for mobile, md: for tablet, lg: for desktop
- Always test at 375px (iPhone SE) and 1280px (desktop)
